# Spring Boot Project Structure 📂

## 📖 What is Spring Boot Project Structure?

A **Spring Boot Project Structure** is the standard directory layout automatically generated by **Spring Initializr**.

It organizes source code, resources, configuration files, and dependencies in a structured way, making the project easy to maintain and scalable.

---

# 🎯 Why is Project Structure Important?

A good project structure helps to:

* ✅ Organize Code
* ✅ Improve Readability
* ✅ Simplify Maintenance
* ✅ Support Team Collaboration
* ✅ Follow Industry Standards

---

# 📂 Default Spring Boot Project Structure

```text
SpringBootProject/
│
├── src/
│   │
│   ├── main/
│   │   │
│   │   ├── java/
│   │   │   └── com/
│   │   │       └── anup/
│   │   │           └── springboot/
│   │   │               ├── SpringBootApplication.java
│   │   │               ├── controller/
│   │   │               ├── service/
│   │   │               ├── repository/
│   │   │               ├── entity/
│   │   │               ├── dto/
│   │   │               ├── config/
│   │   │               ├── exception/
│   │   │               └── util/
│   │   │
│   │   └── resources/
│   │       ├── static/
│   │       ├── templates/
│   │       ├── application.properties
│   │       └── application.yml
│   │
│   └── test/
│       └── java/
│
├── target/
├── pom.xml
├── mvnw
├── mvnw.cmd
└── README.md
```

---

# 📁 src Folder

The `src` folder contains all source code.

```text
src/
│
├── main/
└── test/
```

---

# 📁 src/main/java

Contains all Java source files.

Example:

```text
src/main/java/
        │
        ▼
com.anup.springboot
```

---

# 📁 Main Application Class

This is the entry point of the application.

```java
import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;

@SpringBootApplication
public class SpringBootApplication {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        SpringApplication.run(
            SpringBootApplication.class,
            args
        );

    }
}
```

---

# 📁 Controller Layer

Handles HTTP Requests.

```text
controller/
```

Example:

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/students")
public class StudentController {

}
```

---

# 📁 Service Layer

Contains business logic.

```text
service/
```

Example:

```java
@Service
public class StudentService {

}
```

---

# 📁 Repository Layer

Handles database operations.

```text
repository/
```

Example:

```java
@Repository
public interface StudentRepository {

}
```

Usually extends:

```java
JpaRepository
```

---

# 📁 Entity Layer

Represents database tables.

```text
entity/
```

Example:

```java
@Entity
public class Student {

}
```

---

# 📁 DTO Layer

DTO stands for Data Transfer Object.

Used to transfer data between layers.

```text
dto/
```

Example:

```java
public class StudentDTO {

}
```

---

# 📁 Config Layer

Contains configuration classes.

```text
config/
```

Example:

* Security Configuration
* Swagger Configuration
* Bean Configuration

---

# 📁 Exception Layer

Handles custom exceptions.

```text
exception/
```

Example:

```java
public class ResourceNotFoundException
extends RuntimeException {

}
```

---

# 📁 Utility Layer

Contains helper classes.

```text
util/
```

Examples:

* JWT Utility
* Date Utility
* File Utility

---

# 📁 src/main/resources

Stores application resources.

```text
resources/
│
├── static/
├── templates/
├── application.properties
└── application.yml
```

---

# 📁 static Folder

Contains static files.

Examples:

* CSS
* JavaScript
* Images

```text
static/
├── css/
├── js/
└── images/
```

---

# 📁 templates Folder

Stores HTML templates.

Used with:

* Thymeleaf
* FreeMarker

Example:

```text
templates/
├── index.html
└── login.html
```

---

# 📄 application.properties

Main configuration file.

Example:

```properties
server.port=8080

spring.application.name=StudentManagement

spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/studentdb
```

---

# 📄 application.yml

Alternative configuration file.

```yaml
server:
  port: 8080

spring:
  application:
    name: StudentManagement
```

---

# 📁 src/test/java

Contains unit and integration tests.

Example:

```text
src/test/java/
```

Used with:

* JUnit
* Mockito

---

# 📁 target Folder

Generated automatically after build.

Contains:

* Compiled Classes
* JAR Files
* Temporary Files

Example:

```text
target/
├── classes/
├── test-classes/
└── application.jar
```

---

# 📄 pom.xml

Maven configuration file.

Contains:

* Dependencies
* Plugins
* Build Configuration

Example:

```xml
<dependencies>

    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
    </dependency>

</dependencies>
```

---

# 📄 mvnw and mvnw.cmd

Maven Wrapper files.

They allow running Maven without installing Maven globally.

Run project:

```bash
./mvnw spring-boot:run
```

Windows:

```bash
mvnw.cmd spring-boot:run
```

