---

# 📝 Summary

* Spring Boot follows a standard project structure.
* Java code is stored in `src/main/java`.
* Configuration files are stored in `src/main/resources`.
* `pom.xml` manages dependencies.
* Layered architecture separates responsibilities.
* A well-structured project is easier to maintain and scale.

